## 📊 Production Hardening & Best Practices

| Concern | Solution in Template |
|---------|----------------------|
| **Long Renders (>6h)** | Split workflow: `dispatch` job saves `job_id` to a GitHub Issue/DB. A separate `webhook-triggered` workflow downloads & publishes when notified. |
| **Idempotent Retries** | `dispatch` checks for existing `job_id` in `GITHUB_STATE` before re-submitting. Polling uses exponential backoff. |
| **C2PA Compliance** | Verifies manifest exists before publishing. Fails pipeline if `c2pa_manifest` is missing. |
| **Secret Rotation** | API keys referenced via `${{ secrets.* }}`. Rotate quarterly without breaking workflow syntax. |
| **Cost Control** | `DRY_RUN` input validates schema/format without consuming GPU credits. `QUALITY` dropdown restricts to approved presets. |
| **Artifact Security** | URLs are short-lived. Pipeline downloads immediately & stores in GitHub's encrypted artifact vault. |

